[2] Canada (Edmonton, Alberta)
Date: Fri 25 Apr 2014
Source: CBC (Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) News [edited]
http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/measles-tally-reaches-six-cases-in-edmonton-1.2622418


A new case of measles in Edmonton involving another infant brings the number of cases in the city to 6.

The patient in the latest case involves a child who was too young to have been immunized.

Now health officials are warning people who were in several locations in southeast Edmonton to watch for symptoms. These locations include:
- Zion Baptist Church on [18, 19, and 20 Apr 2014]
- the Ellerslie Road Mac's Store near 84th Street on [19 Apr 2014] from 4 to 7 p.m.
- Alice Produce Garden on 82nd Street on [22 Apr 2014] from 10:30 am to 2 pm

This case is linked to one announced on [19 Apr 2014] involving a child who was travelling from the Philippines to Vancouver and on to Edmonton.

