[3] Canada (Calgary, Alberta)
Date: Thu 24 Apr 2014
Source: Metro News [edited]
http://metronews.ca/news/calgary/1012711/another-measles-case-confirmed-in-calgary/


Health officials have confirmed another case of measles in the Calgary area, Alberta Health Services said [Thu 24 Apr 2014], marking the 8th case in the city so far this year [2014].

"At this time, it is known that this case is not travel related, does not have documentation of immunization, and does involve multiple public exposure settings," provincial officials said in a release.

Those exposure settings include several local restaurants, said Dr Judy MacDonald, the medical officer of health for the Calgary zone.

Health authorities are advising anyone who was at any of the locations at during the time periods listed below that they may have been exposed to measles, and to monitor themselves for symptoms.

Symptoms of measles include a high fever (38.3 deg C [100.9 deg F] or above), a cough, runny nose, red eyes, and a red, blotchy rash that shows up between 3 and 7 days after the fever starts. Typically the rash begins behind the ears and on the face and then spreads down the body.

If symptoms do develop, people are asked to stay at home and to call Health Link Alberta at 1-866-408-5465 before visiting any hospital or other health-care facility.
The exposure locations include:
Asian Buffet - 9125 Bonaventure Drive SE, Calgary
- 8 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 10 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 11 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 12 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 13 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 15 Apr 2014: 11 am to midnight
- 17 Apr 2014: 11 am to 6 pm
Long's Chinese Food - 1448 - 17 Ave S.W., Calgary
- 9 Apr 2014: 6 pm to 10 pm
Castello Ristorante - 405 Spray Avenue, Banff
. 14 Apr 2014: 8 pm to 11:30 pm
South Silk Road Chinese Restaurant - 823 - 14 St NW, Calgary
- 16 Apr 2014: 3:30 pm to 7 pm

[Byline: Robson Fletcher]

