[7] USA (Ohio)
Date: Tue 29 Apr 2014
Source: WCBE (NPR), Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://wcbe.org/post/nearly-two-dozen-measles-cases-confirmed-region


The Ohio Department of Health has now confirmed 21 cases of measles in an outbreak that began in Knox County among unvaccinated Amish who had traveled to the Philippines, which has a measles epidemic.

A total of 19 cases are in Knox County. The other 2 are in nearby Richland and Wayne counties. Officials are urging vaccinations to limit the spread of the disease.

[Byline: Jim Letizia]

