[12] Viet Nam (Ho Chi Minh City): no deaths reported
Date: Fri 25 Apr 2014
Source: TuoiTreNews [edited]
http://tuoitrenews.vn/society/19272/measles-in-national-hub-on-the-rise-no-mortality-reported


Ho Chi Minh City is suffering from a measles outbreak when about 1470 people have caught the disease so far this year [2014], local health authorities announced [Thu 24 Apr 2014].

This is 4 times as much as the figure of the whole year 2013, the city Department of Health said during a meeting organized to discuss measures to cope with the contagion.

From the beginning of the year [2014], measles has affected 1471 people, most of them children, while only about 400 measles cases were recorded in the entire year 2013, Dr. Nguyen Huu Hung, deputy director of the department, said at the event.

Measles has now spread to all 24 districts of the city, Dr Hung said, adding that there have been no reports on deaths associated with measles and its complications in the year to date [24 Apr 2014].

It is worth noting that more and more children who are not required to get vaccination against measles have contracted it, according to the department's statistics.

Last year [2013], children under 3 years old accounted for 90 percent of the total measles cases, the department said. This rate is only 70 percent this year [2014] while the number of children under 10 makes up about 90 percent of the patients. Therefore, the department has recommended that parents should have their kids, aged above 3, vaccinated against measles.

It had earlier suggested that kids of 9 months old to 3 years old should have the vaccination.

Dr Hung said that his agency has provided vaccination against measles to all children from 9 months old to 3 years old citywide, who have yet to be given any injection or just received the 1st of 2 recommended shots.

In addition, city health officials have also extended their vaccination program to children aged 4 to 6, who have been given one or no vaccine shot so far.

Amidst worries over widespread measles, city residents have hurriedly taken their kids to the municipal Pasteur Institute and the local Preventive Health Center for vaccination against the disease over the past several days.

Both children and adults have contracted measles, health authorities said. The HCMC Tropical Diseases Hospital has reported that adults occupy 33 percent (345 people) of the 1031 in-patients treated for measles at the infirmary so far this year [2014].

Nationwide, about 3570 measles cases were found in 61 out of the country's total of 63 cities and provinces as of [23 Apr 2014], the
health ministry said.

Yesterday [24 Apr 2014], 3 more children died of measles, taking its death toll to 131, the ministry announced.

